# OAuth Client IDs and Secrets for Calendar Integration
# These are injected at build time

# Google Calendar OAuth Credentials (Desktop app type)
# Get this from: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret

# Microsoft OAuth Credentials
# Get this from: https://portal.azure.com/#view/Microsoft_AAD_IAM/ActiveDirectoryMenuBlade/~/RegisteredApps
MICROSOFT_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=your-microsoft-client-id
MICROSOFT_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=your-microsoft-client-secret

# Note: Even for Desktop app OAuth clients using PKCE, Google and Microsoft
# still require the client_secret parameter in token exchange requests.
# For public clients like desktop apps, the secret can be embedded in the code.

# For production builds, the TaskNotes official OAuth credentials should be used
# For development/testing, create your own OAuth apps following docs/planning/oauth-setup-guide.md
